Slurm

```json
{
  "application": "Slurm",
  "description": "The script is written for the Slurm workload manager. It uses Slurm commands to submit a job to the cluster. \n  It defines the following settings:\n * job name: myMPI\n * output and error file name: normal_seq_myMPI_1M_thread_1.o\n * number of nodes requested: 1\n * total number of mpi tasks requested: 64\n * partition: largemem512GB\n * run time: 10:00:00 (1.5 hours)\n * email notifications: enabled for job start and finish, sent to chyacinthz@gmail.com\n",
  "software_dependencies": [
    "Intel MPI",
    "Intel compilers (icc, icpc)",
    "Python"
  ],
  "resource_requirements": {
    "nodes": 1,
    "mpi_tasks": 64,
    "partition": "largemem512GB",
    "walltime": "10:00:00"
  },
  "environment_variables": [
    "HMLP_DIR",
    "DYLD_LIBRARY_PATH",
    "LD_LIBRARY_PATH",
    "HMLP_GPU_ARCH",
    "HMLP_ARCH",
    "HMLP_USE_BLAS",
    "QSMLROOT",
    "HMLP_USE_MPI",
    "HMLP_USE_CUDA",
    "HMLP_CUDA_DIR",
    "HMLP_USE_MAGMA",
    "HMLP_MAGMA_DIR",
    "HMLP_ANALYSIS_DATA",
    "OMP_PROC_BIND",
    "OMP_NUM_THREADS",
    "OMP_PLACES",
    "KS_JC_NT",
    "KS_IC_NT",
    "KS_JR_NT"
  ],
  "executable": "testDistributedBoruvka",
  "arguments": [
    "1000000" 
  ]
}
```
